## Stage 2 — Baseline CC–CV

The CC–CV protocol is the industry standard:

| Phase | Control | Duration |
|-------|---------|----------|
| CC | Constant current I = C_rate × Q | Until V = V_max |
| CV | Hold V = V_max | Until I < I_cutoff (e.g. C/20) |

Reference C-rates: 0.5C (slow/safe), 1C (standard), 2C (fast).

---

## Stage 3 — Multi-Stage CC Profiles

Multi-stage protocols apply decreasing C-rates as SOC increases:

```
Stage 1: I₁ = 3C   (SOC 10→50%)
Stage 2: I₂ = 2C   (SOC 50→70%)
Stage 3: I₃ = 1C   (SOC 70→85%)
Stage 4: I₄ = 0.5C (SOC 85→99%)
Final:   CV taper
```

The rationale: high current is safe at low SOC (anode has abundant intercalation sites), but must be reduced as SOC increases to avoid plating.

