## Stage 4 — Optimal Control Formulation

### Problem Statement

```
Minimize:   t_f                        (minimum charging time)
Subject to:
  ẋ = f(x, I)                          (SPM dynamics)
  V(t) ≤ V_max                         (voltage safety)
  θₙ(t) ≤ θ_plating                   (plating constraint)
  T(t) ≤ T_max                         (thermal safety, if coupled)
  0 ≤ I(t) ≤ I_max                     (current bounds)
  SOC(t_f) ≥ SOC_target               (terminal constraint)
  x(0) = x₀                           (initial condition)
```

### Pseudo-Spectral Method (Gauss–Lobatto)

State and control are approximated by Lagrange polynomials on Gauss–Lobatto collocation nodes `{τ₁, ..., τₙ}` on [-1,1]:

```
x(τ) ≈ Σ x(τₖ) Lₖ(τ)
dx/dτ = D × x             (differentiation matrix)
```

Dynamics constraint (collocation): `(2/t_f) D x = f(x, I)` at each node.

This converts the infinite-dimensional OCP into a finite NLP solved with `fmincon` (interior-point algorithm).

### MPC (Model Predictive Control)

At each timestep k, solve a short-horizon subproblem:
```
Minimize:   -Σ I(k+j) × dt              (maximize charge throughput)
Subject to: V(k+j|k) ≤ V_max
            θₙ(k+j|k) ≤ θ_plating
            0 ≤ I(k+j) ≤ I_max
```
Apply I*(k), receive new state, repeat.

